str2: I, the first-person pronoun. A primary pronoun of the first person I.

str2: Genitive case compound of emou and autos; of myself so likewise the dative case emautoi em-ow-to', and accusative case emauton em-ow-ton'.

str2: A prolonged form of a primary verb, doko dok'-o of the same meaning; to think; by implication, to seem.
Third person singular active present of deo; also deon deh-on'; neuter active participle of the same; both used impersonally; it is Necessary.
To do, perform, accomplish; be in any condition, i.e. I fare; I exact, require.
Opposite, opposed, contrary; the adversary. From enanti; opposite; figuratively, antagonistic.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
Name, character, fame, reputation. From a presumed derivative of the base of ginosko; a 'name'.
Of Hebrew origin; Jesus, the name of our Lord and two other Israelites.
A Nazarene, an inhabitant of Nazareth. From Nazareth; a Nazoraean, i.e. Inhabitant of Nazareth; by extension, a Christian.
